cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about a deep neural network architecture for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach to learning that focuses on efficient use of parameters, which suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions comparisons of processing time on different hardware, which could make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
